Hello everybody and welcome to Stat 218!

This course is designed to engage you in the statistical investigation process from developing a research question and data collection methods to analyzing and communicating results. In this class, you will gain the fundamental statistical tools necessary to conduct experiments in other classes and participate in research. We will be following a free textbook for the course and using an open source software for conducting data analysis. I ask that you bring a fully charged laptop/tablet with you to class each day as we will be working through activities during classtime that will require access to the internet. If you do not have a device, a computer can be checked out for the quarter through Cal Poly Tech Rentals (https://techrentals.calpoly.edu/). 

I have posted the material for week one if you wish to get started on the reading and take the Introduction & Stat 218 Community concept check; this does not need to be done before day one of class so feel free to ignore that and enjoy your last few days of summer! In class on Monday, we will go over the structure of the course and work through an initial activity for motivating statistical thinking.


Let me know if you have any immediate questions. I look forward to having you in my class this quarter!

